So let's recap the last 35 minutes we've had together.

00:33:32.300 --> 00:33:35.579
So to recap, models are complex.

00:33:35.579 --> 00:33:39.859
Explainable machine learning is necessary to close the gap between the machine goal

00:33:39.859 --> 00:33:43.420
of output and the human goal of understanding.

00:33:43.420 --> 00:33:47.540
And we need explainability when it's not enough to just get the prediction.

00:33:47.540 --> 00:33:53.459
The model must also justify how it came to the prediction.

00:33:53.459 --> 00:33:58.020
Explainability helps us understand, though, why of models.

00:33:58.020 --> 00:34:04.300
To recap, black boxes are models where you input data and some magic occurs and you get

00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:05.300
an output.

00:34:05.300 --> 00:34:11.340
They're really great for speed running a data science workflow and making really high performing

00:34:11.340 --> 00:34:12.340
models.

00:34:12.340 --> 00:34:16.659
But they're less great when you're trying to understand what's happening in the some

00:34:16.659 --> 00:34:20.659
magic occurs portion of the black box.

00:34:20.659 --> 00:34:26.580
Explainability algorithms help crack open the black box and peer in to see how decisions

00:34:26.580 --> 00:34:29.260
are being made.

00:34:29.260 --> 00:34:33.860
To recap, we have algorithms that focus on feature importance.

00:34:33.860 --> 00:34:39.020
Such as Shapley, which gets a gold star for being able to aggregate feature importance

00:34:39.020 --> 00:34:41.260
both locally and globally.

00:34:41.260 --> 00:34:48.899
We have Lime, which creates a simple and easily understood y equals mx plus b to explain a

00:34:48.899 --> 00:34:50.500
local instance.

00:34:50.500 --> 00:34:56.500
And anchors, which does everything Lime does, but better.

00:34:56.500 --> 00:35:01.760
To recap, we also learned about algorithms that take a look at the cause and effect view

00:35:01.760 --> 00:35:02.939
on a model.

00:35:02.939 --> 00:35:08.739
Such as contrastive explanation methods and counterfactuals.

00:35:08.739 --> 00:35:13.699
To recap, explainability algorithms are just, they're just really cool.

